HEADWORD: Aludel
<hw>Al"u*del</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. & Sp.
<ets>aludel</ets>, fr. Ar. <ets>aluth⟦amac⟧l</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>One of the pear-shaped pots open at both ends,
and so formed as to be fitted together, the neck of one into the bottom
of another in succession; -- used in the process of sublimation.</def>
<rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
